track_notes: I parked through the gate on the Byway, but I have a Subaru Outback with good ground clearance and 4WD.  You may wish to park before the end of the tarmac. Good tracks all the way to the summit. Some boggy bits on the summit plateau.  Trig point for antenna supports.

An alternative (and longer) route from New Radnor.  Not the quickest  route, but useful if you want a circular walk as this can be linked with the normal route from New Radnor.

The Whimble can be short circuited, but the views from the top are too good to miss.  Likewise the out and back to the trig on Bache Hill is optional.

The usual way up from the south.  I walked up using a route over the Whimble and Black Mixen and then used this to go down, making a circular route that took most of the day.  

The path is somewhat indistinct on the plateau like top, but is really quite pleasant lower down.

Total time (including ops): 3hr 40m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Great Rhos Linear from North. Dec 2019.
